parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and violent shaking of the front end of the vehicle can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes violently
often after hitting a bump or uneven pavement
causing the steering wheel to vibrate and making it difficult to control the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or vibrates
making it difficult to control the vehicle
or the vehicle drifts to one side and snaps back to the other side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering pump can cause loss of power steering, making it difficult to control the vehicle, and potentially leading to accidents.
symptoms: The power steering pump fails
causing the steering wheel to become difficult to turn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front end suspension can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates
making it difficult to control the vehicle
or the vehicle has a shimmy or wobble.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The violent shaking of the front end can cause the driver to lose control of the vehicle, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The front end of the vehicle shakes or vibrates violently
often after hitting a bump or pothole
causing the driver to lose control or nearly lose control of the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the EGR cooler and EGR valve can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
hesitates
or loses power
especially when accelerating; thick black smoke appears from the exhaust pipe; white smoke discharges from the engine oil fill tube.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the oil cooler can cause engine failure, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The engine overheats
stalls
or loses power; thick black smoke appears from the exhaust pipe; white smoke discharges from the engine oil fill tube.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the turbo can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls
hesitates
or loses power; no psi for turbo; turbo blows out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the spark plugs can cause engine problems, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The engine ticks or makes a loud noise; spark plugs break off in the head; spark plugs disintegrate upon removal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission slipping can cause the vehicle to lose power and control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates; the vehicle stalls or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to a loss of power and control, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The engine stalls
hesitates
or loses power; the vehicle overheats.
